    <ThingDef ParentName="ITW_ResourceIngredientBase">
        <defName>ITW_PhiMatter</defName>
        <label>phi-matter</label>
        <description>A capacitor-like container filled with phi-matter. Phi-matter is an anomalous material which defies the known laws of physics. While its chaotic properties prevent study, it is theorized that phi-matter is its own elementary particle separate from the rest of the standard model. It forms the basis of all phitech in the galaxy whether made by humans, archotechs, or the Phibearers.\n\nCurrently, the only way to obtain phi-matter is by phi-matter "wells" salvaged from Phibearer ruins; archotechs do not appear to be capable of producing their own equivalents.</description>
        <graphicData>
            <texPath>BaseITW/Things/Item/Resource/ITW_PhiMatter</texPath>
            <graphicClass>Graphic_Single</graphicClass>
        </graphicData>
        <statBases>
            <MaxHitPoints>125</MaxHitPoints>
            <MarketValue>0.5</MarketValue>
        </statBases>
        <tradeTags> <!-- Refer to comment in ITW_MaterialCommon. -->
            <li>ExoticMisc</li>
