    <!-- The NEW big thing this mod is balanced around...!!!!!! -->
    <ThingDef ParentName="ITW_ComponentBase">
        <defName>ITW_PhiWell</defName>
        <label>phi-well</label>
        <description>An ancient and enigmatic device built by the Phibearers over a million years ago. Despite its age, it is as pristine as the day it was made. Through an unknown mechanism, the phi-well accumulates phi-matter inside an internal reservoir, which can then be extracted into capacitor. There is currently no known limit to how much phi-matter any one can generate.\n\nIt will temporarily shut itself off when tampered with, preventing observation or analysis. However, a few insights have been made about its inner workings through indirect observation. Whatever mechanism generates the phi-matter apparently requires a vacuum inside the phi-well. It is aware to some degree of its surroundings, because it can dynamically adjust or even stop phi-matter output depending on any mounted extractor's current ability to withstand phi-matter flow.</description>
        <stackLimit>1</stackLimit>
        <graphicData>
            <texPath>BaseITW/Things/Item/Resource/ITW_PhiWell</texPath>
            <graphicClass>Graphic_Single</graphicClass>
        </graphicData>
        <statBases>
            <Mass>50</Mass>
            <MaxHitPoints>25000</MaxHitPoints>
            <MarketValue>10000</MarketValue>
        </statBases>
        <tradeTags> <!-- Refer to comment in ITW_MaterialCommon. -->
            <li>ExoticMisc</li>
        </tradeTags>
		<comps>
			<li Class="CompProperties_Glower">
				<glowRadius>2</glowRadius>
				<glowColor>(205,190,39,0)</glowColor>
			</li>
		</comps>
        <thingSetMakerTags><li>RewardStandardLowFreq</li></thingSetMakerTags>
    </ThingDef>
    
